Aiko's thesis was on L2 adoption among non-crypto-native users. She spent three months in the Philippines interviewing freelancers paid in USDC on Base. One woman, a transcriptionist, told her: 'Before this, clients would delay two weeks to pay via bank. Now it comes in an hour.' Aiko had come looking for adoption curves. She found something she hadn't expected: dignity. She rewrote her conclusion three times to get it right.

